---
description: Business logic and service layer constraints
globs:
  - "features/**/*"
  - "shared/**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

# services.mdc

- Place reusable business logic inside services or actions
- Avoid business logic directly inside UI components
- Keep services framework-agnnostic where possible
- Keep services deterministic when possible
- Keep side effects isolated
- Separate orchestration from transformation logic
- Avoid mixing persistence logic with presentation logic
- Avoid direct mutation of external state inside services
- Keep async workflows explicit
- Prefer small focused services
- Avoid god-service modules
- Avoid unrelated responsibilities inside a single service
- Keep service inputs explicit
- Keep service outputs predictable
- Prefer typed return values
- Avoid hidden runtime dependencies
- Avoid accessing browser APIs from generic services
- Separate validation from persistence operations
- Keep error handling centralized and predictable
- Avoid duplicated business rules across services
- Prefer pure helper extraction for reusable calculations
- Keep service naming behavior-oriented
- Avoid UI terminology inside service modules